{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-A8HG1CNG","@type":"Concept","title":"Knowledge graph as single source of truth","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"All structured metadata lives in the knowledge graph rather than in document frontmatter, separate databases, or ad-hoc files. Views (graph queries) replace traditional documents like SRS, test plans, and traceability matrices. The graph uses JSON-LD compact form serialized as JSON Lines (JSONLT), with 12 node types connected by 15 predicates following INCOSE-inspired systems engineering practices.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-PYNZNBT9","@type":"Concept","title":"Formal transformation chain","conceptType":"process","status":"crystallized","summary":"Work follows a formal transformation chain: concept → need → requirement → task → deliverable. Each step produces derivesFrom edges maintaining full traceability. Concepts capture exploration and design thinking. Needs formalize stakeholder expectations. Requirements state verifiable obligations. Tasks break requirements into executable work. This chain ensures nothing is built without knowing why, and nothing is required without knowing who needs it.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},{"@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-QGFDVM3W","@type":"Concept","title":"Phase-gated module lifecycle","conceptType":"process","status":"crystallized","summary":"Each module tracks its current lifecycle phase independently: architecture → design → implementation → integration → verification → validation. Phase gates enforce quality criteria before advancement: all tasks for the current phase must complete and no blocking defects (critical/major) can remain open. Cross-module coordination uses task dependencies and baseline policies rather than synchronized phases.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF"},{"@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-QP3MN68X","@type":"Concept","title":"Hook-based policy enforcement","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"Declarative policies intercept Claude Code tool execution through a six-stage evaluation pipeline. Policies match events, evaluate CEL conditions, and produce admission decisions (allow, deny, warn) or mutations. Deny-wins aggregation ensures the most restrictive matching policy controls. Fail-open semantics guarantee that errors in policy evaluation never block Claude Code. The daemon amortizes expensive operations across invocations.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-SFR9SMSS"},{"@id":"MOD-K7S0T58A"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-PQMJE5T6","@type":"Concept","title":"Skills and subagents encode methodology","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"Development methodology is encoded as Claude Code skills and subagents rather than just documentation. Skills use preprocessing commands to inject live graph context at load time and instructed commands for interactive graph queries during execution. Subagents provide isolated execution contexts for workflows like review where context separation matters. Both use arci CLI commands as the interface to the graph.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-MFGQ1YYT","@type":"Concept","title":"Single binary, three modes","conceptType":"architectural","status":"crystallized","summary":"One Go binary serves all roles: command-line tool, daemon, and dashboard. No version skew between components. The CLI operates in direct execution mode (loads config, evaluates locally) or daemon delegation mode (forwards to daemon API). This simplifies distribution and eliminates coordination problems between separately versioned components.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-K6NBQ0KW"},{"@id":"MOD-K7S0T58A"},{"@id":"MOD-0TXTB3JK"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"CON-25739MMV","@type":"Concept","title":"Bootstrapping arci with arci","conceptType":"process","status":"exploring","summary":"arci is built using its own methodology before the tooling exists to enforce it. Stage 0 uses manual graph editing and Claude Code skills as shell scripts. Stage 1 builds the graph engine and CLI to replace manual operations. Stage 2 adds hook enforcement. Each stage produces tooling that the next stage uses, validating the ontology under real conditions.","informs":[{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"}],"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0","@type":"Developer","title":"Tony","status":"active","description":"Project creator and primary developer. GitHub: tbhb.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z"}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-0TXTB3JK","@type":"Module","title":"Dashboard","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Web-based diagnostics dashboard for live event streaming, policy testing, state browsing, coverage reports, and graph browsing.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-C72RBTMP","@type":"Module","title":"Workflows","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Agent interaction layer: skills, subagents, and workflow orchestration that encode arci's development methodology as structured instructions for Claude Code.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-K6NBQ0KW","@type":"Module","title":"CLI","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Command-line interface for hook evaluation, graph management, developer commands, and daemon/dashboard/MCP control. Operates in direct execution mode or daemon delegation mode.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-K7S0T58A","@type":"Module","title":"Daemon","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Long-running process with config cache, compiled policies, connection pooling, REST API, WebSocket events, and hot-reload. Amortizes expensive operations across many requests.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-QRN0SQCF","@type":"Module","title":"Graph","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Knowledge graph engine: typed nodes, JSON-LD serialization, JSONLT persistence, graph algorithms, validation, lifecycle state machines, phase constraints, and transformation chain enforcement.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-SFR9SMSS","@type":"Module","title":"Hooks","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Policy engine and Claude Code hook integration. Policy compilation, six-stage evaluation pipeline, admission decisions with deny-wins aggregation, fail-open semantics, and built-in policies for development discipline enforcement.","childOf":{"@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1"},"created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"MOD-YC2QPMX1","@type":"Module","title":"arci","status":"active","phase":"architecture","description":"Agentic Requirements Composition & Integration. A framework for Claude Code that combines policy-driven hooks with spec-driven development, providing declarative rules to validate, transform, and control tool execution alongside an INCOSE-inspired knowledge graph.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"STK-C2B6R1GY","@type":"Stakeholder","title":"arci contributor","status":"active","concerns":"Clean architecture, testability, clear module boundaries, well-documented ontology, contribution-friendly codebase.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"STK-RKZJ8SWT","@type":"Stakeholder","title":"Policy author","status":"active","concerns":"Policies are debuggable, testable, and composable. Clear documentation of the policy model, expression language, and evaluation semantics.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
{"@context":"context.jsonld","@id":"STK-W1329EGF","@type":"Stakeholder","title":"Developer using Claude Code","status":"active","concerns":"Policies don't block workflow unexpectedly. Graph provides useful context that improves agent output. Skills encode best practices without requiring deep systems engineering knowledge.","created":"2026-03-01T00:00:00Z","attributedTo":{"@id":"DEV-9CPASKT0"}}
